---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="Yann Bonarchi Simeu — software engineer building banking infrastructure in Central Africa, on the road from engineering to leadership.">
  <article class="wrap prose">
    <span class="ledger-no">00</span>
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p class="lede">
      I'm a software engineer based in Cameroon. I build banking and fintech
      systems for the CEMAC region — the kind of infrastructure that has to be
      right the first time, because money is on the line.
    </p>

    <!-- TODO: rewrite this in your own voice. Keep it first-person and honest.
         Anchor to Cameroon. Do NOT name confidential employer projects. -->
    <p>
      My path started in code: shipping core banking features, integrating
      mobile money rails, and learning — sometimes the hard way — what it takes
      to run software that a whole region depends on. Working from Central
      Africa shapes how I think. Constraints here are real: connectivity,
      regulation under the BEAC, the leap-frog dynamics of mobile money. They
      force a kind of engineering discipline that I've come to value.
    </p>

    <p>
      I'm now studying for a Bachelor of Science in Business Administration at
      the University of the People, deliberately. I want the vocabulary and the
      models of business to match the systems I already know how to build. The
      arc I'm walking is engineering → IT leadership → building something of my
      own.
    </p>

    <p>
      This site is where the two halves meet: the work I've shipped, and the
      thinking behind it. If any of it is useful to you, that's the point.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
    <ul class="links">
      <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/">LinkedIn</a> — where I post regularly</li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/">GitHub</a> — public code</li>
      <li><a href="mailto:skybdev@gmail.com">Email</a> — reach me directly</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</Base>

